World Health Organization in Africa is currently hosting briefing on ramping up preparedness for COVID-19 vaccine roll-out in Africa. JOHANNEBSURG - The World Health Organisation in Africa holds an online media briefing on what countries on the continent will have to do in terms of ramping up their preparedness for the COVID19 rollout. On Wednesday, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize has confirmed the country is now officially experiencing its second wave of Covid-19 infections. WATCH: COVID-19: Health minister announces SA in second wave The minister has expressed concern at the increasing number of infections in the country. Mkhize says four provinces are the primary contributors to the second wave as there is a surge in infection numbers in those provinces.